# P1-F12.3: the diffs that must never be skimmed.
#
# A change request Reeve files may be built by a coding agent, and most of what
# it touches is ordinary application code. These paths are not: they can disable
# the CI gates, alter data irreversibly, or reach credentials. Requiring the
# repository owner's review on them means an agent-authored diff here is looked
# at, not waved through.
#
# This only bites once branch protection requires review from code owners on
# these paths. Everything else stays as-is.

/.github/workflows/          @chris-88
/supabase/migrations/        @chris-88
/supabase/functions/         @chris-88
/scripts/check-bundle.mjs    @chris-88
/scripts/check-test-accounts.mjs @chris-88
